Mapam forward controls to give a little more relaxed riding position. It has a K&N air filter inside the air box, and Barnett Heavy Duty Clutch springs have been added. The wheels and hubs have been professionally powder-coated black to match the paint, with the spokes being left natural aluminum color. Brand new front & rear Dunlop Wide Whitewalls with less than 2000 miles on them. Also numerous chrome items have been added like switch housings, new wide-style levers, Cobra 2" pullback risers, riser clamp, master cylinder cover, radiator cover, horn cover, coolant cap cover. This bike currently has the Memphis Shades brand full fairing with the short 5" black windshield. Memphis Shades Honda Shadow mounting brackets for said fairing. Hogtunes Audio system with handlebar mount for an MP3, or satellite radio receiver. National Cycle Cruiseliner Hard Saddlebags and their respective mounting brackets. These last 3 parts the fairing, Hogtunes system, and the hard bags alone would cost you over $1600 to purchase separately. This bike is only 750CC, but it's very powerful and everyone always mistakes it for at least an 1100CC just looking at it. It's quick off the line and all the way up to 70 and it fits in with the big boys. This is a very well taken care of bike, I would rate it a 9 out of 10. This bike is a great looking bagger, so if you want a nice bike without the big price you owe it to yourself to at least come take a look at this bike. title: For Sale:  NEW, NEVER FIRED ROSSI R92 CARBINE LEVER ACTION - 45 LONG COLT
postcontent:
MSRP:  $559

Ringo had one. Rooster had one. Lucas had one. Josh Randall had part of one. Yes, all of these screen heroes had a Winchester Model 92. Who can ever forget the scene in Stagecoach as John Wayne as Ringo twirls his '92 Winchester to stop the stage. Or perhaps the greatest scene ever in any Western as Rooster Cogburn with a Colt Single Action Army .45 in his left hand and a freshly twirled .44-40 Winchester in his right hand yells "Fill your hand you sonnavabitch!" and prepares to meet the Ned Pepper gang single-handedly.

Most of us grew up watching Chuck Connors as The Rifleman twirl his large loop lever Model '92 to cock it and then operate it like a semi- automatic on the streets of North Fork. Steve McQueen, as the bounty hunter Josh Randall in Wanted: Dead or Alive also carried a bastardized Model 92 with a short barrel and shorter stock. The eye-catching loop lever was there along with someone's idea of what the little '92 should carry as ammunition as Randall's belt was filled with .45-70 cartridges that would not even come close to fitting the Model 92.

The Rossi R92 Round Barrel delivers a shorter, lighter version of its big brothers with this 16 inch carbine models.  All R92 Round Barrel models feature crescent buttplates and an extended front sight. 

Excellent for brush hunting and wilderness packing.
